			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">When we discussed this, there was some concern that setting "align 1" on floating point loads/stores would produce too much slowdown on ARM.  We need to measure this.  JF says that ARM's vld1.8/vst1.8 will be slower than vldr/vstr.

However, setting "align 1" on integer loads/stores seemed to be uncontroversial.

I'll take on the task of adding an IR pass to change the align attributes.
